cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about relation extraction using deep neural models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel framework for learning with limited labeled data, which involves training a neural network, making it likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for matching rules with sentences, making cs.IR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for learning, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
